- I don't want to, I'm serious.

09:04.208 --> 09:07.000
Alexander the Great had
diamond-tipped arrows made for him.

09:07.250 --> 09:10.083
They could go through
a Mongol's head.

09:10.916 --> 09:13.416
These arrows couldn't
puncture a cat's head...

09:13.875 --> 09:15.958
...but they'll pierce the cube.

09:16.750 --> 09:18.541
But what's the point?

09:19.958 --> 09:22.583
I need to know
I can trust you.

09:22.875 --> 09:24.666
You can.

09:50.375 --> 09:51.875
- What are you doing, asshole?
- You moved!

09:52.125 --> 09:53.750
- You could've hit me in the eye!
- You told me to do it!

09:54.000 --> 09:56.041
- You could've hit me in the eye!
- What happened?

09:56.291 --> 09:58.083
- Nothing.
- Wilson shot at my head.

09:58.333 --> 10:00.541
- Why did you shoot at his head?
- It's not true.

10:00.791 --> 10:02.375
- I thought I could trust you.
- You can.

10:02.583 --> 10:05.500
- So, why did you shoot at me?
- Why did you shoot at him?

10:05.750 --> 10:07.541
I didn't.

10:07.791 --> 10:10.375
Shorty, they're fighting out there.
Lalo doesn't want to pay.

10:10.625 --> 10:12.291
Who said you could
call me that?

10:12.583 --> 10:14.375
I'd go out if I were you,
Shorty.

10:14.625 --> 10:17.291
- I thought I could trust you.
- You can.

10:17.583 --> 10:19.666
So why did you shoot me
in the head?

10:25.541 --> 10:26.375
Can I borrow it?

10:26.458 --> 10:27.291
THE HARD LIFE OF AN EASY WOMAN

10:28.250 --> 10:32.208
No, Scherezada Rios stays here.
It's a hard one to find.

10:33.541 --> 10:37.166
All right, if you don't pay,
you can't play.

10:38.041 --> 10:39.291
What's up, Lalo?

10:39.625 --> 10:42.375
Lalo has been playing
and hasn't paid yet.

10:42.625 --> 10:46.208
Pay up, Lalo, don't be a dick.
Oh, you don't want to pay?

10:46.958 --> 10:50.791
In that case, move it.
Move aside, let me--

10:51.791 --> 10:53.541
Is that level 15?

10:54.541 --> 10:55.791
Wait a minute.

10:57.333 --> 10:58.958
I'll cover you.

10:59.208 --> 11:03.541
But just this once, got it?
We can't set a precedent, Camila.

11:06.250 --> 11:09.041
This isn't a game, fuckers.
We must think like the enemy.

11:09.416 --> 11:11.416
As if we came from another planet.

11:12.125 --> 11:15.541
When King Pakal returns in his ship
and everything comes to an end...

11:15.708 --> 11:18.125
...don't say I didn't warn you,
you little shits.

11:18.833 --> 11:21.500
- Juan, you're still here?
- No!

11:21.583 --> 11:23.916
They're waiting for you!

11:24.291 --> 11:28.083
- Ben, are you staying for dinner?
- I can't, my dad needs me.

11:28.333 --> 11:31.583
- How is he doing?
- Good, they put him on oxygen.

11:31.875 --> 11:34.958
I'm really sorry.
Give him one of the fruitcakes.

11:35.250 --> 11:38.625
- My daughter made them.
- Don't use English words, Mom.

11:39.041 --> 11:41.625
You can say fruitcake
in Spanish, you know?

11:41.875 --> 11:44.583
Julio is waiting for you.
It's about the--

11:47.333 --> 11:48.583
The Santa costume?

11:48.958 --> 11:53.083
- I don't want to, Mom.
- Juan, come here.

11:53.916 --> 11:57.500
No, Juan, I keep tucking it in,
but it's still too big on you.

11:57.833 --> 12:00.541
It's hard to believe you are
Dr. Juan's grandson.

12:01.083 --> 12:05.041
You should dress as an elf,
it would fit you better.

12:06.750 --> 12:09.166
They've informed us that
the Modern Art Museum...

12:09.416 --> 12:12.291
...and the Anthropology Museum
will remain closed...

12:12.541 --> 12:15.041
...from today until
January 5th...

12:15.291 --> 12:17.916
...while a new ventilation system
is being installed.

12:18.166 --> 12:21.958
They're working day and night
to be ready when school starts.

12:22.291 --> 12:26.666
So, this holiday season
there will be no museums.

12:26.958 --> 12:29.625
- Can I use your phone?
- Wait, don't move yet.

12:29.875 --> 12:31.958
- Let me finish.
- It's fine like this.

12:32.208 --> 12:33.750
Put it on Mom's tab!

12:38.416 --> 12:39.500
GUARDHOUSE

12:42.583 --> 12:43.583
ACETONE

12:44.166 --> 12:45.041
HARDWARE STORE

12:50.291 --> 12:52.083
- Duct tape?
- Yes, duct tape.

12:52.333 --> 12:53.833
- How many nails?
- A bunch.

12:54.083 --> 12:57.291
- Thin copper wire, six meters.
- Six meters copper wire.

12:57.625 --> 12:59.041
That's too much.

12:59.333 --> 13:01.041
- Alligators?
- What are those?

13:01.291 --> 13:03.791
Oh, the crocodiles!
