13:07.166 --> 13:09.125
- Do you have any acetone?
- What?

13:09.541 --> 13:10.791
Ether?

13:13.666 --> 13:15.416
Since Juan was a kid,
every Christmas...

13:15.666 --> 13:20.250
...his grandfather dressed as Santa
and gave out presents after dinner.

13:21.333 --> 13:25.250
He died that year, so everyone
agreed Juan would take over.

13:25.833 --> 13:29.250
Juan protested, saying he'd rather
dress as Quetzatcoatl...

13:30.125 --> 13:34.500
...because Santa Claus was a tool
to indoctrinate kids into capitalism.

13:34.833 --> 13:37.125
His protests went ignored.

13:41.833 --> 13:43.458
Take a deep breath.

13:59.666 --> 14:00.916
Get dressed.

14:01.333 --> 14:04.000
Your blood pressure
and resting heart rate are high.

14:05.500 --> 14:09.125
- I'm prescribing you some pills.
- You did that already.

14:10.291 --> 14:11.541
Hey, Dad...

14:13.208 --> 14:15.708
I need to use your car,
can I borrow it?

14:16.125 --> 14:19.375
I have something important to do
after Christmas dinner.

14:21.291 --> 14:23.125
What are we going to do
with you, bud?

14:23.375 --> 14:26.791
I already paid the deposit
for the place at the mall.

14:27.333 --> 14:31.875
- I'm pretty much set to go.
- You're not a veterinarian yet.

14:33.125 --> 14:35.583
I know that.
I'm graduating soon.

14:37.000 --> 14:40.541
- I'm not like Uncle Oscar.
- Did you pick up the suit?

14:40.916 --> 14:45.916
Yeah, I even got it tailored.
It's going to fit great.

14:47.083 --> 14:48.708
Dad?

14:56.916 --> 14:58.666
Am I dying soon, Dad?

15:00.500 --> 15:01.750
Yes?

15:02.583 --> 15:04.291
Yes, sweetie, show her in.

15:07.625 --> 15:11.000
So I guess I'll see you
tonight, yeah?

15:12.375 --> 15:14.375
You'll be there, right?

15:18.208 --> 15:20.250
- I just filled the tank.
- Thanks.

15:20.583 --> 15:23.458
- Thank you.
- Hey, Chiva.

15:24.250 --> 15:28.291
- Time for you annual drug test?
- Anal, yes. Pretty wild.

15:28.625 --> 15:30.458
Try it, you might like it.

15:30.708 --> 15:34.583
- Dad said work calls only.
- What? What did Dad say?

15:34.916 --> 15:37.666
- What did he say?
- Let go of me, asshole.

16:17.666 --> 16:19.041
- Hello?
- Wilson?

16:19.666 --> 16:21.791
Where have you been all day?
It has to be tonight.

16:22.041 --> 16:23.458
What?

16:23.791 --> 16:25.833
What do you mean "what"?

16:26.583 --> 16:29.583
- But it's Christmas.
- So?

16:30.041 --> 16:33.250
- You said the 31st.
- It has to be tonight.

16:33.541 --> 16:37.125
- You said New Year's Eve.
- I just saw the news.

16:37.208 --> 16:41.166
Repairs start tomorrow,
it's going to be crowded.

16:41.250 --> 16:43.208
- It has to be tonight.
- Are we even ready?

16:43.291 --> 16:45.208
Sure we're ready,
we've gone over and over it.

16:45.333 --> 16:47.916
I already called Bosco,
I got the car, everything.

16:49.416 --> 16:52.625
Yeah, but I can't tonight.
I'm having dinner with Dad.

16:52.708 --> 16:55.375
I'm not asking, moron.

16:55.625 --> 16:59.625
I'm not asking you to fucking prom.
You're coming tonight.

16:59.875 --> 17:03.375
I guess we'll have to see
because...

17:03.708 --> 17:06.665
...the doctor said it might be
his last Christmas.

17:07.665 --> 17:11.083
Look, I'll see you at midnight
at the usual place.

17:11.374 --> 17:13.665
- Yes, Juan.
- Don't be late.

17:13.749 --> 17:15.249
We'll see.

17:15.458 --> 17:16.665
Hello?

17:17.040 --> 17:19.915
- What are you up to, Shorty?
- Nothing.

17:20.083 --> 17:22.624
Eeny, meeny, miney, mo.
Catch a tiger by the toe.

17:22.915 --> 17:25.540
If he hollers, let him go.

17:25.790 --> 17:28.583
One, two, three, four...

17:29.000 --> 17:31.500
One, two...

17:31.875 --> 17:35.958
Why don't you hide here?
Get under the table.

17:36.500 --> 17:38.041
No one will find you.

17:38.291 --> 17:40.458
I saw you, under the chair!

17:40.708 --> 17:42.291
You're mistaken,
there's no one here.

17:42.541 --> 17:45.625
Hey, have you met
Oscar's girlfriend?

17:45.916 --> 17:50.583
- He has a girlfriend?
- Why else ask for another seat?

17:51.125 --> 17:53.916
- What?
- There's no more ham.

17:54.875 --> 17:57.375
Don't fill up with snacks.
Wait a little.

17:57.625 --> 18:00.666
Have some cheese and olives.
Don't fill up before dinner.

18:00.916 --> 18:03.958
- She's his student!?
- We'll meet her soon.

18:04.500 --> 18:08.000
- What is this stuff?
- It's pâté, thank you very much.

18:13.041 --> 18:16.333
Hello! Merry Christmas!
This is Gaby.

18:16.791 --> 18:18.208
Gaby, my family.

18:18.625 --> 18:20.875
- Who's your guest?
- This is Gaby.

18:21.208 --> 18:23.541
- Introduce us.
- Hello.

18:23.708 --> 18:26.083
- My brother.
- Nice to meet you.

18:26.333 --> 18:28.875
- Uncle Oscar, how are you?
- I'm fine.

18:29.291 --> 18:30.875
I'll take your bag.

18:31.416 --> 18:34.416
- Hi, nice to meet you.
- The lady of the house.

18:35.583 --> 18:37.333
- My niece.
- Susana!

18:37.583 --> 18:41.208
- It's Christmas, they're dating.
- Precisely, it's Christmas!

18:41.500 --> 18:44.666
Good evening, sir.
I brought bread and cider.

18:50.875 --> 18:52.833
This one has a bite mark!

18:55.250 --> 18:58.166
- Neto was hungry.
- Must've been the baker!

18:58.416 --> 19:01.458
- Did you taste that one, too!
- No, it's unopened!

19:02.208 --> 19:04.500
- Really, it is!
- He says it's unopened.

19:22.333 --> 19:24.291
Shorty, where are you going
with those bags?

19:24.541 --> 19:26.416
- It's your kids, chopped up.
- Asshole.

19:26.666 --> 19:29.416
- I'm dumping them in the dam.
- Don't joke about that!

19:29.708 --> 19:32.666
- What do you want, chipmunk?
- Dad asked why you're here...

19:32.916 --> 19:34.708
...instead of downstairs,
with everyone.

19:35.041 --> 19:37.291
Why do you always
isolate yourself?

19:37.583 --> 19:39.833
- Aren't you happy?
- It's Christmas, why would I be happy?

19:40.125 --> 19:42.416
You should be thankful,
you have a family.

19:42.708 --> 19:46.166
- Some people don't, but you do.
- Thank you, family.

19:46.416 --> 19:49.416
Are you doing Grandpa's thing?
Did the suit fit you?

19:49.833 --> 19:51.250
I bet it didn't.

19:51.500 --> 19:56.041
It was too big on you.
I'm sure it looks huge on you.

19:56.458 --> 19:59.250
If it was green instead,
you'd be a nice elf.

19:59.541 --> 20:03.333
If you do it, do it right.
It's very important you do it right.

20:03.625 --> 20:07.041
- Don't screw up.
- You smell like period blood.

20:07.458 --> 20:10.500
You smell like baby shit,
you fucking dwarf.

20:23.208 --> 20:25.041
Make way for the turkey!

20:29.541 --> 20:31.833
Give a round of applause for the cook!

20:32.875 --> 20:34.375
Everyone, hush!

20:34.666 --> 20:36.500
- Please, sit down.
- Children, sit down!

20:40.666 --> 20:43.125
I just want to say...

20:44.166 --> 20:47.208
...that this has been
a terrible year.

20:48.125 --> 20:53.791
I want you to join me in a toast
to someone very special...

20:55.500 --> 20:58.083
...to my father.
Thank you, cheers!

20:58.375 --> 21:00.958
- Cheers, cheers.
- To Grandpa!

21:01.333 --> 21:04.375
- To Grandpa.
- And to your joy as well.

21:04.666 --> 21:07.625
And to the joys
this year brought us!

21:08.416 --> 21:10.291
...its scales will dry up.

21:10.666 --> 21:16.041
No, Keiko means "lucky one,"
it doesn't bring you luck.

21:16.958 --> 21:19.625
So kids can see it!
It was in Sea Wo--

21:19.916 --> 21:21.916
- It was in Sea World, right?
- Norway.

21:22.166 --> 21:24.125
- It was in Norway.
- In the sea.

21:24.375 --> 21:26.125
- Norway?
- Yeah, right?

21:26.416 --> 21:29.000
It's so that people
can have a good time.

21:29.250 --> 21:32.125
We went there recently.
We loved it, it was great.

21:32.416 --> 21:35.125
But he was asking why
bring it now?

21:35.333 --> 21:38.250
It definitely has to be
a smoke screen.

21:38.708 --> 21:42.791
The park can do whatever
they like with their money.

21:43.625 --> 21:48.166
- It's a private company.
- The government can't interfere.

21:48.458 --> 21:51.208
But how can you deny
state involvement...

21:51.583 --> 21:53.875
...if they closed up
the freeway...

21:54.125 --> 21:59.333
...so that two huge trucks could
move the orca to the park...

21:59.833 --> 22:02.916
- ...before its scales dried up?
- Whales don't have scales.

22:03.583 --> 22:06.791
- Got it?
- Having fun in the Pacific...

22:07.083 --> 22:10.291
...and waking up in Mexico City
is not good luck.

22:10.583 --> 22:13.416
But why do it now?

22:13.666 --> 22:17.166
Why, at this point for the country,
with the peso as low as it is...

22:17.541 --> 22:20.375
...and ties between the cartels
and the government?

22:20.583 --> 22:23.916
- Enlighten us, Juan.
- Juan, do you know about orcas?

22:24.458 --> 22:27.500
- What?
- About orcas, like Keiko.

22:27.833 --> 22:31.416
Hey, Christmas, right here!
We're having a conversation.

22:31.791 --> 22:34.833
Don't worry, you can go
play Atari with the kids...

22:35.083 --> 22:38.250
...while the rest of us grown ups
talk about politics.

22:38.625 --> 22:41.166
- Keiko will die there.
- It will?

22:41.416 --> 22:44.625
Then, they'll chop him up
and sell him outside the park.

22:45.333 --> 22:46.875
Yeah, fish tacos!

22:49.375 --> 22:52.333
Did you know they live
with their mothers?

22:52.625 --> 22:54.958
